From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 17:20:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 05/12] drm/msm/dp: Do not fail audio prepare when DP is
 inactive

Userspace can probe all HDMI/DP PCM devices exposed by an ALSA card while
building its profile set. For example, UCM-aware servers may try to open
every DP PCM even when only one connector is currently plugged in.

msm_dp_audio_prepare() currently returns -EINVAL when the DP controller is
not powered. This protects against unclocked register access, but it also
makes the inactive DP PCM fail during probing. If one such PCM is part of
a UCM profile, the whole profile can be discarded even though jack and ELD
state already mark the inactive connector as unavailable.

Keep the clock-safety check, but treat an inactive controller as a no-op:
skip the DP audio register programming and return success. Active streams
still program the hardware as before, while unplugged or disabled outputs
remain discoverable and report their availability through the usual jack
and ELD controls.

Fixes: 158b9aa74479 ("drm/msm/dp: wait for audio notification before disabling clocks")
Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
(cherry picked from commit accb24e72b38599de949ab61c4fc03c11cbf8812)
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c | 15 +++++----------
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
index 41018e82efa1..af7b72dd896c 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
@@ -277,17 +277,12 @@ int msm_dp_audio_prepare(struct drm_bridge *bridge,
 	msm_dp_display = to_dp_bridge(bridge)->msm_dp_display;
 
 	/*
-	 * there could be cases where sound card can be opened even
-	 * before OR even when DP is not connected . This can cause
-	 * unclocked access as the audio subsystem relies on the DP
-	 * driver to maintain the correct state of clocks. To protect
-	 * such cases check for connection status and bail out if not
-	 * connected.
+	 * Userspace can probe DP PCMs while the connector is unplugged or
+	 * disabled. The controller clocks are off then, so skip register
+	 * programming; jack and ELD state still report sink availability.
 	 */
-	if (!msm_dp_display->power_on) {
-		rc = -EINVAL;
-		goto end;
-	}
+	if (!msm_dp_display->power_on)
+		return 0;
 
 	audio = msm_dp_audio_get_data(msm_dp_display);
 	if (IS_ERR(audio)) {
